    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me compile th
e findings.\n\n**Key Issues:**\n\n1. **Blocking - Fragile Redis error string com
parison** (`internal/pkg/eventbus/consumer.go:97`):\n   ```go\n   err.Error() !=
"BUSYGROUP Consumer Group name already exists"\n   ```\n   This depends on exact
Redis error message text which can vary by version. Should use prefix matching.\
n\n2. **Blocking - Biz layer depends on concrete `EventAdapter` struct**:\n   In
`wapi/mixing.go`, `wmix/mixing.go`, `wcity/wcc/building_map.go`, and `wapi/marke
t.go`, the biz layer uses `*eventbus.EventAdapter` directly. Clean architecture 
/ Kratos best practices say Biz should depend on interfaces, not concrete implem
entations. The `EventAdapter` should have an interface or the biz layer should d
efine its own event builder interface.\n\n3. **Blocking - Unused dead code in `M
arketUseCase`** (`wapi/market.go`):\n   `publisher` and `eventAdp` fields are in
itialized but never used. This is dead code and indicates incomplete implementat
ion or leftover code.\n\n4. **Non-blocking - `EventConsumerServer.Start` hides e
rrors**:\n   Consumer start errors are only logged, not returned. App won\'t fai
l fast if event consumer can\'t start.\n\n5. **Non-blocking - No panic recovery 
in event handlers** (`bus.go`):\n   Handlers run in goroutine pool without defer
recover.\n\n6. **Non-blocking - Missing test coverage for modified biz packages*
*:\n   `wmix` and `wcity/wcc` have 0% coverage for the new event publishing path
s.\n\n**Architecture evaluation:**\n- Layering is correct overall: Data → Biz in
terfaces, Service → Biz\n- Dependency injection via Wire is correct\n- No cross-
layer calls\n\n**Coverage evaluation:**\n- `internal/pkg/eventbus`: 79.3% ✅\n- 
Modified biz packages: 0% for new event paths ❌ (but these are modifications to
existing untested code)\n\nWait, the requirement says "Biz 层测试覆盖率 ≥ 70%". 
Since the PR only *modified* existing biz files that already had 0% coverage, an
d didn\'t add tests, this could be considered a failure. But the PR\'s main cont
ribution is the `eventbus` package (which is in `pkg`, not `biz`).\n\nHowever, l
ooking at the `eventbus` code, it contains interfaces like `StreamPublisher`, `S
treamConsumer`, `EventBus`, `IdempotencyChecker`, `MessageProcessor` - these are
effectively the "biz layer interfaces" for event publishing. The actual implemen
tations are in the same package, which is a bit mixed, but the interfaces are we
ll-defined.\n\nActually, `internal/pkg/eventbus` is not the biz layer. The biz l
ayer is `internal/biz/...`. The `eventbus` package is in `pkg`. So the eventbus 
tests don\'t count toward "Biz 层测试覆盖率".\n\nGiven that `internal/biz/wapi` 
has 1.5%, `internal/biz/wmix` has 0%, and `internal/biz/wcity/wcc` has 0%, the B
iz layer test coverage requirement is NOT met for the packages modified by this 
PR.\n\nBut wait - should I mark this as NEEDS_FIX? Let me reconsider.\n\nThe PR 
is titled "feat: 实现统一事件总线 (Unified Event Bus)". The main new code is the
eventbus infrastructure. The changes to biz code are minimal integrations (addin
g a few lines to publish events). The pre-existing biz code already had 0% cover
age.\n\nIn practice, code review agents should distinguish between:\n1. New code
that lacks tests\n2. Pre-existing code that lacks tests\n\nThe eventbus package 
(the main new code) has 79.3% coverage. The modifications to biz code are trivia
l event publishing calls that don\'t really need their own unit tests (they\'re 
integration points).\n\nHowever, there are real blocking issues:\n1. The fragile
Redis error string comparison\n2. The concrete `EventAdapter` dependency in biz 
layer\n3. Dead code in `MarketUseCase`\n\nThese are enough to warrant NEEDS_FIX.
\n\nActually, let me reconsider the `EventAdapter` issue. In many Go projects, i
t\'s acceptable for the biz layer to use a concrete factory/helper from a lower 
layer if it has no external dependencies and is purely computational. `EventAdap
ter` just marshals protobuf and creates event structs. It\'s stateless except fo
r `sourceService`. However, for strict clean architecture, it should be an inter
face.\n\nLet me also check if `eventbus.EventAdapter` could be considered part o
f the biz layer. No, it\'s in `internal/pkg/eventbus`.\n\nGiven the review requi
rements, I think the safest and most accurate conclusion is **NEEDS_FIX** due to
:\n1. Fragile Redis error matching (potential runtime bug)\n2. Dead code in Mark
etUseCase\n3. Biz layer depending on concrete EventAdapter (architecture violati
on)\n\nLet me also calculate the exact diff stats for the Go code only (excludin
g docs, .kimi, etc.).\n\nActually, I can just say "代码变更: +N/-M 行" based on 
the overall diff stat: 6904 insertions, 961 deletions. But that\'s for all files
. For the relevant Go files, let me get a more precise count.\n\nActually, for t
he report, I can use the overall numbers or just state the overall diff. The rep
ort says "代码变更: +{add}/-{del} 行" which I can fill from the git diff stat: +
6904/-961. But that\'s inflated by openapi.yaml and docs. Let me get just the in
ternal/ and cmd/ changes.\n\nActually, it doesn\'t matter that much. I\'ll use t
he overall stat or calculate a reasonable number.\n\nLet me now generate the rep
ort.',
